---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Payerset LLC Privacy Policy"
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative bg-brand-dark-deep overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-dark to-brand-dark-deep"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24 lg:py-32">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-semibold text-white leading-tight">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg sm:text-xl text-slate-300">
          Last Updated 7/5/2024
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-8">

        <!-- Intro -->
        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          To protect your privacy better, Payerset LLC wants our customers, suppliers, employees, applicants, and other relevant parties to know how we collect personal data, the types of personal data we collect, and how we use and share your personal data. This Privacy Policy ("Policy") describes how Payerset LLC ("Payerset," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses your personal information when you use our services, including our website and any other products or services we offer. By using our services, you agree to this Policy and consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein. This Policy does not apply to third-party products, services, or businesses governed under separate terms, agreement, or privacy policy, or that are otherwise not offered under Payerset's express agreements, regardless of whether they integrate with or interact with our products ("Third-Party Services").
        </p>

        <!-- What We Do and Information We Collect -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">What We Do and Information We Collect</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We are aggregating data and/or using data analytics in our service, and we may collect the following types of information when you use our services:
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-6">Personal Information:</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We collect personal information you provide when creating an account, such as your name, email address, username, password, and other account information. We may also collect information about your usage of our services, including search queries, data access, and other interactions with our services.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-6">Device and Usage Information:</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            We collect information about the devices you use to access our services, such as IP addresses, browser types, operating system versions, and other device-related information. We may also collect usage data, such as the date and time of your access, pages viewed, and other usage statistics.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Cookies -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Cookies</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            We may automatically collect non-personally identifiable information and data using cookies or similar technology. Cookies are small text files a website uses to recognize repeat users, facilitate the user's ongoing access to the website and facilitate the use of the website. Cookies also allow a website to track usage behavior and compile website usage information that will allow for the improvement of content and target advertising. Most browsers allow You to control cookies, including whether to accept them and how to remove them. You may set Your browsers to notify you if You receive a cookie, or You may choose to block cookies with your browser. However, please be aware that some features of our Website and Services may not function or may be slower if you refuse cookies. You may also get cookies from our advertisers or other third parties with links on the Website as described below. We do not directly control these cookies. The use of advertising cookies sent by third party ad servers is standard in the internet industry. Some cookies will remain on your computer after you have left the Website. We may use the services of third parties to collect and use anonymous information about your visits to and interactions with our website using technologies such as cookies to personalize advertisements for goods and services.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- How We Use Your Information -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed pl-4">
            <li>To provide, maintain, and improve our services;</li>
            <li>To personalize your experience and provide you with relevant content and advertisements;</li>
            <li>To communicate with you about our services, including updates, promotions, and other relevant information;</li>
            <li>To monitor and analyze usage trends and preferences;</li>
            <li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues and security incidents;</li>
            <li>To comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms of Use; and</li>
            <li>For any other purpose for which you provide consent.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Disclosure of Your Information -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may disclose your information to third parties in the following circumstances:
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-6">Service Providers:</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may share your information with third-party service providers who perform functions on our behalf, such as data hosting, analytics, and customer support.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-6">Legal Compliance and Protection of Rights:</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We may disclose your information as required by law, regulation, legal process, government request or to protect the rights, property, or safety of Payerset, our users, or others; or to address fraud, security or technical issues.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-6">Business Transfers:</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            In the event of a merger, acquisition, reorganization, or sale of assets, we may transfer your information to the acquiring entity, subject to the same confidentiality obligations and restrictions on use as set forth in this Policy.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-6">With Your Consent:</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            We may disclose your information for any other purpose with your consent.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Security -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Data Security</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures, such as encryption and access controls, to safeguard your information. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Retention -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. When we no longer need your information for these purposes, we will securely delete or anonymize it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Eligibility -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Eligibility</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            To access and use our service, you must be at least 18 years old. By using our service, you represent and warrant that you meet this age requirement, and that you have the legal capacity and authority to enter into a binding contract.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Your Rights and Choices -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Your Rights and Choices</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You may have certain rights under applicable data protection laws, such as the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information, or to object to the processing of your information for certain purposes. To exercise these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@payerset.com" class="text-brand-primary hover:text-brand-primary-hover transition-colors">info@payerset.com</a>. We will respond to your request within a reasonable timeframe and in accordance with applicable laws.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            In addition, you may choose to opt-out of receiving promotional communications from us by following the unsubscribe instructions included in each communication or by contacting us at the email address provided above. Please note that even if you opt-out of receiving promotional communications, we may still send you important service-related communications, such as updates or security alerts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Changes to This Policy -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            We reserve the right to modify this Policy at any time, and we will post the updated Policy on our website. It is your responsibility to regularly review this Policy to stay informed of any changes. Your continued use of our services after the date of any changes to this Policy constitutes your acceptance of the new Policy. If you do not agree to the changes, you must stop using our services and notify us of your decision to terminate your account or subscription.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Entire Agreement -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Entire Agreement</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            This Policy is the entire agreement between the parties. This Policy incorporates by reference the Terms of Use, which contains a choice of law provision. The choice of law provision in the Terms of Use is incorporated here by reference.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact Us -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            If you have any questions about this Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@payerset.com" class="text-brand-primary hover:text-brand-primary-hover transition-colors">info@payerset.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Copyright -->
        <div class="pt-8 border-t border-slate-200">
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
            Copyright &copy; 2024 Payerset LLC. All rights reserved.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
